-- Turkey Plans to Cut Public Spending in 2013 Budget, Star Reports
-- B y   S e l c u k   G o k o l u k
-- 2012-08-22T06:45:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-22/turkey-plans-to-cut-public-spending-in-2013-budget-star-reports.html
Turkey’s government won’t allow new
non-strategic projects and is seeking to cut public spending as
the  Finance Ministry  drafts a budget for next year, the Star
newspaper  reported , without saying where it got the information.  The government wants to keep expenditures below 400 billion
liras ($222 billion) by lowering public spending in 2013, the
Istanbul-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Selcuk Gokoluk in Istanbul at 
